description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a flexible and efficient receptionist to join the theatres administration team. Working across all areas of the department (Main Theatres and Day Surgery), you will be enthusiastic, highly organised and an effective member of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be focused on providing a high level of customer service to both patients and colleagues. The ability to multi task and work in more than one area on a daily basis is a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have a good all-round education including GCSE Grade C or equivalent in English Language and Mathematics and a minimum of 2 years’ experience in a busy office environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will be required to work Wednesday 12:30-16:30, Thursday &amp; Friday 07:00-16:30 although flexibility on hours/days would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be Thursday 26th November and Friday 27th November.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sam King, Admin Lead &amp; Project Support Manager sam.king5@nhs.net 01722 336262 x 2268&lt;/p&gt;
